text: Nevertheless, they shall be servants to him, that they may know my service and the service of the kingdoms of the countries."

text: So Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem. He took away the treasures of the house of the LORD and the treasures of the king's house. He took away everything. He also took away the shields of gold that Solomon had made,
verse_text: 2 Paralipomenon 12.9 Recessit itaque Sesac rex AEgypti ab Jerusalem, sublatis thesauris domus Domini et domus regis: omniaque secum tulit, et clypeos aureos quos fecerat Salomon:

text: And when he humbled himself the wrath of the LORD turned from him, so as not to make a complete destruction. Moreover, conditions were good in Judah.
verse_text: 2 Paralipomenon 12.12 Verumtamen quia humiliati sunt, aversa est ab eis ira Domini, nec deleti sunt penitus: siquidem et in Juda inventa sunt opera bona.

text: Now the acts of Rehoboam, from first to last, are they not written in the chronicles of Shemaiah the prophet and of Iddo the seer? There were continual wars between Rehoboam and Jeroboam.
verse_text: 2 Paralipomenon 12.15 Opera vero Roboam prima et novissima scripta sunt in libris Semeiae prophetae, et Addo videntis, et diligenter exposita: pugnaveruntque adversum se Roboam et Jeroboam cunctis diebus.

text: The rest of the acts of Abijah, his ways and his sayings, are written in the story of the prophet Iddo.
verse_text: 2 Paralipomenon 13.22 Reliqua autem sermonum Abia, viarumque et operum ejus, scripta sunt diligentissime in libro Addo prophetae.

text: And Asa did what was good and right in the eyes of the LORD his God.
verse_text: 2 Paralipomenon 14.2 Fecit autem Asa quod bonum et placitum erat in conspectu Dei sui, et subvertit altaria peregrini cultus, et excelsa.

verse_text: 2 Paralipomenon 14.3 Et confregit statuas, lucosque succidit:

text: The acts of Asa, from first to last, are written in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel.
verse_text: 2 Paralipomenon 16.11 Opera autem Asa prima et novissima scripta sunt in libro regum Juda et Israel.

text: And Judah assembled to seek help from the LORD; from all the cities of Judah they came to seek the LORD.

text: This is the thing that you shall do: of you priests and Levites who come off duty on the Sabbath, one third shall be gatekeepers,

text: Now after the death of Jehoiada the princes of Judah came and paid homage to the king. Then the king listened to them.
verse_text: 2 Paralipomenon 24.17 Postquam autem obiit Jojada, ingressi sunt principes Juda, et adoraverunt regem: qui delinitus obsequiis eorum, acquievit eis.

text: The men of Judah captured another 10,000 alive and took them to the top of a rock and threw them down from the top of the rock, and they were all dashed to pieces.

text: Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, lived fifteen years after the death of Joash the son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel.

text: Now the rest of the deeds of Amaziah, from first to last, are they not written in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel?
verse_text: 2 Paralipomenon 25.26 Reliqua autem sermonum Amasiae priorum et novissimorum scripta sunt in libro regum Juda et Israel.

text: And he did what was right in the eyes of the LORD, according to all that his father Amaziah had done.

text: A wind has wrapped them in its wings, and they shall be ashamed because of their sacrifices.
verse_text: Hosea 4.19 Ligavit eum spiritus in alis suis, et confundentur a sacrificiis suis.

text: "Come, let us return to the LORD; for he has torn us, that he may heal us; he has struck us down, and he will bind us up.
verse_text: Hosea 6.2 quia ipse cepit, et sanabit nos; percutiet, et curabit nos.

text: After two days he will revive us; on the third day he will raise us up, that we may live before him.
verse_text: Hosea 6.3 Vivificabit nos post duos dies; in die tertia suscitabit nos, et vivemus in conspectu ejus. Sciemus, sequemurque ut cognoscamus Dominum: quasi diluculum praeparatus est egressus ejus, et veniet quasi imber nobis temporaneus et serotinus terrae.

text: But they do not consider that I remember all their evil. Now their deeds surround them; they are before my face.
verse_text: Hosea 7.2 Et ne forte dicant in cordibus suis, omnem malitiam eorum me recordatum, nunc circumdederunt eos adinventiones suae: coram facie mea factae sunt.

text: For with hearts like an oven they approach their intrigue; all night their anger smolders; in the morning it blazes like a flaming fire.
verse_text: Hosea 7.6 Quia applicuerunt quasi clibanum cor suum, cum insidiaretur eis; tota nocte dormivit coquens eos: mane ipse succensus quasi ignis flammae.

text: Strangers devour his strength, and he knows it not; gray hairs are sprinkled upon him, and he knows it not.
verse_text: Hosea 7.9 Comederunt alieni robur ejus, et ipse nescivit; sed et cani effusi sunt in eo, et ipse ignoravit.

text: They utter mere words; with empty oaths they make covenants; so judgment springs up like poisonous weeds in the furrows of the field.
verse_text: Hosea 10.4 Loquimini verba visionis inutilis, et ferietis foedus; et germinabit quasi amaritudo judicium super sulcos agri.

text: From the days of Gibeah, you have sinned, O Israel; there they have continued. Shall not the war against the unjust overtake them in Gibeah?
verse_text: Hosea 10.9 Ex diebus Gabaa peccavit Israel; ibi steterunt. Non comprehendet eos in Gabaa praelium super filios iniquitatis.

text: The sword shall rage against their cities, consume the bars of their gates, and devour them because of their own counsels.
verse_text: Hosea 11.6 Coepit gladius in civitatibus ejus, et consumet electos ejus, et comedet capita eorum.

text: My people are bent on turning away from me, and though they call out to the Most High, he shall not raise them up at all.
verse_text: Hosea 11.7 Et populus meus pendebit ad reditum meum; jugum autem imponetur eis simul, quod non auferetur.

text: A merchant, in whose hands are false balances, he loves to oppress.
verse_text: Hosea 12.7 Chanaan, in manu ejus statera dolosa, calumniam dilexit.

text: The pangs of childbirth come for him, but he is an unwise son, for at the right time he does not present himself at the opening of the womb.
verse_text: Hosea 13.13 Dolores parturientis venient ei: ipse filius non sapiens: nunc enim non stabit in contritione filiorum.

text: Take with you words and return to the LORD; say to him, "Take away all iniquity; accept what is good, and we will pay with bulls the vows of our lips.
verse_text: Hosea 14.3 Tollite vobiscum verba, et convertimini ad Dominum; et dicite ei: Omnem aufer iniquitatem, accipe bonum, et reddemus vitulos labiorum nostrorum.

text: I will heal their apostasy; I will love them freely, for my anger has turned from them.
verse_text: Hosea 14.5 Sanabo contritiones eorum; diligam eos spontanee: quia aversus est furor meus ab eis.

text: O Ephraim, what have I to do with idols? It is I who answer and look after you. I am like an evergreen cypress; from me comes your fruit.
verse_text: Hosea 14.9 Ephraim, quid mihi ultra idola? Ego exaudiam, et dirigam eum ego ut abietem virentem; ex me fructus tuus inventus est.

text: And you shall go out through the breaches, each one straight ahead; and you shall be cast out into Harmon," declares the LORD.
verse_text: Amos 4.3 Et per aperturas exibitis altera contra alteram, et projiciemini in Armon, dicit Dominus.

text: Hear this word that I take up over you in lamentation, O house of Israel:
verse_text: Amos 5.1 Audite verbum istud, quod ego levo super vos planctum: domus Israel cecidit, et non adjiciet ut resurgat.

text: But let justice roll down like waters, and righteousness like an ever-flowing stream.
verse_text: Amos 5.24 Et revelabitur quasi aqua judicium, et justitia quasi torrens fortis.

text: Therefore they shall now be the first of those who go into exile, and the revelry of those who stretch themselves out shall pass away."

text: For behold, the LORD commands, and the great house shall be struck down into fragments, and the little house into bits.
verse_text: Amos 6.12 Quia ecce Dominus mandabit, et percutiet domum majorem ruinis, et domum minorem scissionibus.

text: Do horses run on rocks? Does one plow there with oxen? But you have turned justice into poison and the fruit of righteousness into wormwood
verse_text: Amos 6.13 Numquid currere queunt in petris equi, aut arari potest in bubalis? quoniam convertistis in amaritudinem judicium, et fructum justitiae in absinthium.

text: you who rejoice in Lo-debar, who say, "Have we not by our own strength captured Karnaim for ourselves?"

text: "For behold, I will raise up against you a nation, O house of Israel," declares the LORD, the God of hosts; "and they shall oppress you from Lebo-hamath to the Brook of the Arabah."
verse_text: Amos 6.15 Ecce enim suscitabo super vos, domus Israel, dicit Dominus Deus exercituum, gentem, et conteret vos ab introitu Emath usque ad torrentem deserti.

text: Then Jonah prayed to the LORD his God from the belly of the fish,
verse_text: Jonah 2.2 Et oravit Jonas ad Dominum Deum suum de ventre piscis,

text: The waters closed in over me to take my life; the deep surrounded me; weeds were wrapped about my head
verse_text: Jonah 2.6 Circumdederunt me aquae usque ad animam: abyssus vallavit me, pelagus operuit caput meum.

text: at the roots of the mountains. I went down to the land whose bars closed upon me forever; yet you brought up my life from the pit, O LORD my God.
verse_text: Jonah 2.7 Ad extrema montium descendi; terrae vectes concluserunt me in aeternum: et sublevabis de corruptione vitam meam, Domine Deus meus.

text: Those who pay regard to vain idols forsake their hope of steadfast love.
verse_text: Jonah 2.9 Qui custodiunt vanitates frustra, misericordiam suam derelinquunt.

text: But I with the voice of thanksgiving will sacrifice to you; what I have vowed I will pay. Salvation belongs to the LORD!"
verse_text: Jonah 2.10 Ego autem in voce laudis immolabo tibi: quaecumque vovi, reddam pro salute Domino.

text: And the LORD spoke to the fish, and it vomited Jonah out upon the dry land.
verse_text: Jonah 2.11 Et dixit Dominus pisci, et evomuit Jonam in aridam.

text: Pass on your way, inhabitants of Shaphir, in nakedness and shame; the inhabitants of Zaanan do not come out; the lamentation of Beth-ezel shall take away from you its standing place.
verse_text: Micah 1.11 Et transite vobis, habitatio pulchra, confusa ignominia: non est egressa quae habitat in exitu: planctum domus vicina accipiet ex vobis, quae stetit sibimet.

text: Therefore you will have none to cast the line by lot in the assembly of the LORD.
verse_text: Micah 2.5 Propter hoc non erit tibi mittens funiculum sortis in coetu Domini.

text: "Do not preach"- thus they preach- "one should not preach of such things; disgrace will not overtake us."
verse_text: Micah 2.6 Ne loquamini loquentes; non stillabit super istos, non comprehendet confusio.

text: Should this be said, O house of Jacob? Has the LORD grown impatient? Are these his deeds? Do not my words do good to him who walks uprightly?
verse_text: Micah 2.7 Dicit domus Jacob: Numquid abbreviatus est spiritus Domini, aut tales sunt cogitationes ejus? nonne verba mea bona sunt cum eo qui recte graditur?

text: and I will cut off the cities of your land and throw down all your strongholds;
verse_text: Micah 5.11 Et perdam civitates terrae tuae, et destruam omnes munitiones tuas: et auferam maleficia de manu tua, et divinationes non erunt in te:

text: and I will cut off sorceries from your hand, and you shall have no more tellers of fortunes;
verse_text: Micah 5.12 et perire faciam sculptilia tua et statuas tuas de medio tui, et non adorabis ultra opera manuum tuarum:

text: and I will cut off sorceries from your hand, and you shall have no more tellers of fortunes;
verse_text: Micah 5.11 Et perdam civitates terrae tuae, et destruam omnes munitiones tuas: et auferam maleficia de manu tua, et divinationes non erunt in te:

text: and I will root out your Asherah images from among you and destroy your cities.
verse_text: Micah 5.14 Et faciam, in furore et in indignatione, ultionem in omnibus gentibus quae non audierunt.

text: And in anger and wrath I will execute vengeance on the nations that did not obey.
verse_text: Micah 5.14 Et faciam, in furore et in indignatione, ultionem in omnibus gentibus quae non audierunt.

text: From you came one who plotted evil against the LORD, a worthless counselor.
verse_text: Nahum 1.11 Ex te exibit cogitans contra Dominum malitiam, mente pertractans praevaricationem.

text: They are dreaded and fearsome; their justice and dignity go forth from themselves.
verse_text: Habakkuk 1.7 Horribilis et terribilis est: ex semetipsa judicium et onus ejus egredietur.

text: At kings they scoff, and at rulers they laugh. They laugh at every fortress, for they pile up earth andtake it.
verse_text: Habakkuk 1.10 Et ipse de regibus triumphabit, et tyranni ridiculi ejus erunt; ipse super omnem munitionem ridebit, et comportabit aggerem, et capiet eam.

text: Then they sweep by like the wind and go on, guilty men, whose own might is their god!"
verse_text: Habakkuk 1.11 Tunc mutabitur spiritus, et pertransibit, et corruet: haec est fortitudo ejus dei sui.

text: He brings all of them up with a hook; he drags them out with his net; he gathers them in his dragnet; so he rejoices and is glad.
verse_text: Habakkuk 1.15 Totum in hamo sublevavit, traxit illud in sagena sua, et congregavit in rete suum. Super hoc laetabitur, et exsultabit.

text: You stripped the sheath from your bow, calling for many arrows. Selah You split the earth with rivers.
verse_text: Habakkuk 3.9 Suscitans suscitabis arcum tuum, juramenta tribubus quae locutus es; fluvios scindes terrae.

text: "I will utterly sweep away everything from the face of the earth," declares the LORD.
verse_text: Zephaniah 1.2 Congregans congregabo omnia a facie terrae, dicit Dominus:

verse_text: Zephaniah 2.1 Convenite, congregamini, gens non amabilis,

text: And you, O seacoast, shall be pastures, with meadows for shepherds and folds for flocks.

text: Woe to her who is rebellious and defiled, the oppressing city!

text: I will gather those of you who mourn for the festival, so that you will no longer suffer reproach.

text: "Speak now to Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and to Joshua the son of Jehozadak, the high priest, and to all the remnant of the people, and say,
verse_text: Haggai 2.3 Loquere ad Zorobabel, filium Salathiel, ducem Juda, et ad Jesum, filium Josedec, sacerdotem magnum, et ad reliquos populi, dicens:

text: Yet now be strong, O Zerubbabel, declares the LORD. Be strong, O Joshua, son of Jehozadak, the high priest. Be strong, all you people of the land, declares the LORD. Work, for I am with you, declares the LORD of hosts,
verse_text: Haggai 2.5 Et nunc confortare, Zorobabel, dicit Dominus; et confortare, Jesu, fili Josedec, sacerdos magne; et confortare, omnis populus terrae, dicit Dominus exercituum: et facite (quoniam ego vobiscum sum, dicit Dominus exercituum)

text: according to the covenant that I made with you when you came out of Egypt. My Spirit remains in your midst. Fear not.
verse_text: Haggai 2.6 verbum quod pepigi vobiscum cum egrederemini de terra AEgypti: et spiritus meus erit in medio vestrum: nolite timere.

text: For thus says the LORD of hosts: Yet once more, in a little while, I will shake the heavens and the earth and the sea and the dry land.
verse_text: Haggai 2.7 Quia haec dicit Dominus exercituum: Adhuc unum modicum est, et ego commovebo caelum, et terram, et mare, et aridam.

text: And I will shake all nations, so that the treasures of all nations shall come in, and I will fill this house with glory, says the LORD of hosts.
verse_text: Haggai 2.8 Et movebo omnes gentes, et veniet desideratus cunctis gentibus: et implebo domum istam gloria, dicit Dominus exercituum.

text: The silver is mine, and the gold is mine, declares the LORD of hosts.
verse_text: Haggai 2.9 Meum est argentum, et meum est aurum, dicit Dominus exercituum.

text: On the twenty-fourth day of the ninth month, in the second year of Darius, the word of the LORD came by Haggai the prophet,
verse_text: Haggai 2.11 In vigesima et quarta noni mensis, in anno secundo Darii regis, factum est verbum Domini ad Aggaeum prophetam, dicens:

text: "Thus says the LORD of hosts: Ask the priests about the law:
verse_text: Haggai 2.12 Haec dicit Dominus exercituum: Interroga sacerdotes legem, dicens:

text: 'If someone carries holy meat in the fold of his garment and touches with his fold bread or stew or wine or oil or any kind of food, does it become holy?'" The priests answered and said, "No."
verse_text: Haggai 2.13 Si tulerit homo carnem sanctificatam in ora vestimenti sui, et tetigerit de summitate ejus panem, aut pulmentum, aut vinum, aut oleum, aut omnem cibum, numquid sanctificabitur? Respondentes autem sacerdotes, dixerunt: Non.

text: Then Haggai said, "If someone who is unclean by contact with a dead body touches any of these, does it become unclean?" The priests answered and said, "It does become unclean."
verse_text: Haggai 2.14 Et dixit Aggaeus: Si tetigerit pollutus in anima ex omnibus his, numquid contaminabitur? Et responderunt sacerdotes, et dixerunt: Contaminabitur.

text: Now then, consider from this day onward. Before stone was placed upon stone in the temple of the LORD,
verse_text: Haggai 2.16 Et nunc ponite corda vestra a die hac et supra, antequam poneretur lapis super lapidem in templo Domini.

text: how did you fare? When one came to a heap of twenty measures, there were but ten. When onecame to the wine vat to draw fifty measures, there were but twenty.
verse_text: Haggai 2.17 Cum accederetis ad acervum viginti modiorum, et fierent decem; et intraretis ad torcular, ut exprimeretis quinquaginta lagenas, et fiebant viginti.

text: I struck you and all the products of your toil with blight and with mildew and with hail, yet you did not turn to me, declares the LORD.
verse_text: Haggai 2.18 Percussi vos vento urente, et aurugine, et grandine omnia opera manuum vestrarum: et non fuit in vobis qui reverteretur ad me, dicit Dominus.

text: Consider from this day onward, from the twenty-fourth day of the ninth month. Since the day that the foundation of the LORD's temple was laid, consider:
verse_text: Haggai 2.19 Ponite corda vestra ex die ista, et in futurum, a die vigesima et quarta noni mensis: a die qua fundamenta jacta sunt templi Domini, ponite super cor vestrum.

text: The word of the LORD came a second time to Haggai on the twenty-fourth day of the month,
verse_text: Haggai 2.21 Et factum est verbum Domini secundo ad Aggaeum in vigesima et quarta mensis, dicens:

text: "Speak to Zerubbabel, governor of Judah, saying, I am about to shake the heavens and the earth,
verse_text: Haggai 2.22 Loquere ad Zorobabel ducem Juda, dicens: Ego movebo caelum pariter et terram,

text: and to overthrow the throne of kingdoms. I am about to destroy the strength of the kingdoms of the nations, and overthrow the chariots and their riders. And the horses and their riders shall go down, every one by the sword of his brother.
verse_text: Haggai 2.23 et subvertam solium regnorum, et conteram fortitudinem regni gentium: et subvertam quadrigam et ascensorem ejus, et descendent equi, et ascensores eorum, vir in gladio fratris sui.

text: And the angel of the LORD solemnly assured Joshua,

text: And the word of the LORD came to me:

text: and so I make you despised and abased before all the people, inasmuch as you do not keep my ways but show partiality in your instruction."
verse_text: Malachi 2.9 Propter quod et ego dedi vos contemptibiles, et humiles omnibus populis, sicut non servastis vias meas, et accepistis faciem in lege.

text: He will sit as a refiner and purifier of silver, and he will purify the sons of Levi and refine them like gold and silver, and they will bring offerings in righteousness to the LORD.
verse_text: Malachi 3.3 et sedebit conflans, et emundans argentum: et purgabit filios Levi, et colabit eos quasi aurum et quasi argentum, et erunt Domino offerentes sacrificia in justitia.

text: Then the offering of Judah and Jerusalem will be pleasing to the LORD as in the days of old and as in former years.

text: From the days of your fathers you have turned aside from my statutes and have not kept them. Return to me, and I will return to you, says the LORD of hosts. But you say, 'How shall we return?'
verse_text: Malachi 3.7 A diebus enim patrum vestrorum recessistis a legitimis meis, et non custodistis: revertimini ad me, et revertar ad vos, dicit Dominus exercituum. Et dixistis: In quo revertemur?

text: Will man rob God? Yet you are robbing me. But you say, 'How have we robbed you?' In your tithes and contributions.
verse_text: Malachi 3.8 Si affliget homo Deum, quia vos configitis me? Et dixistis: In quo configimus te? In decimis et in primitiis.

text: You are cursed with a curse, for you are robbing me, the whole nation of you.
verse_text: Malachi 3.9 Et in penuria vos maledicti estis, et me vos configitis gens tota.

text: Bring the full tithes into the storehouse, that there may be food in my house. And thereby put me to the test, says the LORD of hosts, if I will not open the windows of heaven for you and pour down for you a blessing until there is no more need.
verse_text: Malachi 3.10 Inferte omnem decimam in horreum, et sit cibus in domo mea: et probate me super hoc, dicit Dominus: si non aperuero vobis cataractas caeli, et effudero vobis benedictionem usque ad abundantiam:

text: Then all nations will call you blessed, for you will be a land of delight, says the LORD of hosts.
verse_text: Malachi 3.12 Et beatos vos dicent omnes gentes: eritis enim vos terra desiderabilis, dicit Dominus exercituum.

text: "Your words have been hard against me, says the LORD. But you say, 'How have we spoken against you?'

text: And now we call the arrogant blessed. Evildoers not only prosper but they put God to the test and they escape.'"
verse_text: Malachi 3.15 Ergo nunc beatos dicimus arrogantes: siquidem aedificati sunt facientes impietatem, et tentaverunt Deum, et salvi facti sunt.

text: Then those who feared the LORD spoke with one another. The LORD paid attention and heard them, and a book of remembrance was written before him of those who feared the LORD and esteemed his name.

text: Then once more you shall see the distinction between the righteous and the wicked, between one who serves God and one who does not serve him.

text: But for you who fear my name, the sun of righteousness shall rise with healing in its wings. You shall go out leaping like calves from the stall.
